@page "/"

<PageTitle>WitDatabase Blazor WASM Sample</PageTitle>

<div class="card">
    <h1>&#128190; WitDatabase Blazor WASM Sample</h1>
    <p>
        This sample demonstrates using <strong>WitDatabase</strong> in a Blazor WebAssembly application
        with full IndexedDB persistence support.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="card" style="background: #d4edda; border-color: #28a745;">
    <h3>? Full Async Support Complete!</h3>
    <p>
        <strong>IndexedDB storage is now fully functional!</strong> All BTree operations have been refactored 
        to support async I/O, enabling seamless persistence in Blazor WebAssembly.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>What works:</strong>
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>? In-memory storage (full functionality)</li>
        <li>? IndexedDB persistence (full functionality)</li>
        <li>? BTree async operations (Search, Insert, Update, Delete, Range Scan)</li>
        <li>? Transactions with async commit/rollback</li>
        <li>? Encryption (AES-GCM)</li>
        <li>? Automatic async-only storage detection</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h3>Features Demonstrated</h3>
    
    <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="crud">CRUD Operations</a></strong> - Basic Create, Read, Update, Delete operations with IndexedDB</li>
        <li><strong><a href="transactions">Transactions</a></strong> - Transaction support with async commit/rollback</li>
        <li><strong><a href="encryption">Encryption</a></strong> - AES-GCM encryption at rest</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h3>Storage Options</h3>
    
    <table class="data-table">
        <thead>
